es. The volume thus examines the contradictions at play when the necessary claim for transculturality meets the institutions of the nation-state.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 4aColonialism. 4aCultural History. 4aMemory Culture. 4aMuseology. 4aMuseum Management. 4aMuseum. 4aMuseums. 4aNation State. 4aSociety. 4aTransculturality. 7aART / Museum Studies.2bisacsh  aColonialism.  aCultural History.  aMemory Culture.  aMuseology.  aMuseum Management.  aMuseum.  aMuseums.  aNation State.  aSociety.  aTransculturality.1 aDávila, Sebastián Eduardo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGinwala, Natasha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHanna, Monica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKahlon, Rajkamal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeeb, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeeb, Susanne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMilevska, Suzana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSamuel, Nina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSamuel, Nina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aShatanawi, Mirjam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSingh, Kavita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpero Adotevi, Stanislas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWitcomb, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 20